label.value: endocrine cell of the adult ring gland

value.value: An endocrine cell that is located in the adult ring gland.
Any epithelial cell of the adult.
Any epithelial cell of the larva.
Cell that forms the wall of the adult dorsal vessel. There are 84 of these cells per dorsal vessel (Lehmacher et al., 2012).
A cardiomyocyte whose contraction contributes to the pumping of the dorsal vessel. These cells make up most of the wall of the dorsal vessel (Lehmacher et al., 2012).

definition.value: Likely to be the ppk23 cells, as null mutants lose leg and proboscis responses to pheromones, however, function of ppk23 in wing margin was not investigated. (Thistle et al., 2012 - FBrf0218411). ppk23 cells are distinct from sugar and water cells, but a few cells coexpress Gr66a and ppk23 (Thistle et al., 2012). Some ppk23 cells also express ppk29, but not clear from Thistle et al. (2012) whether this is all or a subset.

value.value: Neuron of the late embryo or larva that is responsive to the presence of pheromones (Mast et al., 2014; Narasimha et al., 2019).

definition.value: Many of these appear to be octopaminergic based on Tdc2-GAL4 expression (Pauls et al., 2018 - FBrf0240407).

A specialized cardiomyocyte that is part of an ostium in the wall of the dorsal vessel (Lehmacher et al., 2012). There are two ostial cells per ostium (Lehmacher et al., 2012).
Any epithelial cell (FBbt:00000124) that is part of some testis sheath (FBbt:00004955).

Cell of the epithelium lining the adult crop. These cells are of ectodermal origin and produce the cuticular lining of the crop system (Stoffolano Jr and Haselton, 2013).

label.value: adult lamina neuropil associated glial cell

value.value: Glial cell located in the lamina neuropil (Kremer et al., 2017).
Any visceral muscle cell (FBbt:00005070) that is part of some midgut (FBbt:00005383).
Any visceral muscle cell (FBbt:00005070) that is part of some foregut (FBbt:00005379).
Any fat cell (FBbt:00046052) that is part of some adult pericerebral fat mass (FBbt:00048409).
A monolayer epithelium forming the wall of the ejaculatory bulb (Guiraudie-Capraz et al., 2007).
Cell of the epithelium of the ejaculatory bulb. It secretes the male pheromone cis-vaccenyl acetate (cVA) (Guiraudie-Capraz et al., 2007).
A monolayer epithelium forming the wall of the anterior and posterior ejaculatory ducts (Bairati, 1968).
Cell of the epithelium of the ejaculatory duct. It secretes antimicrobial peptides such as Drosomycin and Andropin (Samakovlis et al., 1991; Ferrandon et al., 1998).

A squamous monolayer epithelium that lines the oviduct. Its cells are joined along their lateral membranes by extensive septate junctions, but lack apical zonal adherens junctions (Kapelnikov et al., 2008).
Epithelial cell of the oviduct. It has convoluted intracellular membranous structures and extensive microvilli, suggestive of a role in secretion (Middleton et al., 2006).

label.value: intestinal stem cell of the adult midgut-hindgut boundary

value.value: An intestinal stem cell at the posterior end of the adult midgut, near the boundary with the hindgut. These cells are not part of the midgut-hindgut hybrid zone, but are located within 30 um of it and may re-populate it upon injury. They express frizzled3 (Sawyer et al., 2017).

label.value: epithelial cell of the adult midgut-hindgut hybrid zone

value.value: Cell of the adult gut epithelium at the boundary between the midgut and the hindgut. There are approximately 125 of such cells in mature adults (day 4), down from 300 during pupation. They express wingless, along with markers characteristic of both the midgut and the hindgut (Sawyer et al., 2017).

Any epithelial cell (FBbt:00000124) that is part of some adult foregut epithelium (FBbt:00047164).
Any epithelial cell (FBbt:00000124) that is part of some adult pyloric epithelium (FBbt:00007044).
Any gut epithelial section (FBbt:00047124) that is part of some adult esophagus (FBbt:00003131).
Any epithelial cell (FBbt:00000124) that is part of some adult esophagus epithelium (FBbt:00058279).
A three-layered epithelium lining the adult proventriculus (King, 1988).
Cell of the epithelium lining the adult proventriculus. These cells varies in height from low cuboidal in the inner layer to tall columnar in parts of the intermediate and outer layers (King, 1988).

Ostial cell of the adult dorsal vessel. There are 20 of these cells per dorsal vessel, forming 5 pairs of ostia along the dorsal vessel. The 4 cells of the posterior-most pair of ostia are embryonic/larval ostial cells that persist in the adult stage; the other 16 cells differentiate during metamorphosis (Lehmacher et al., 2012; Rotstein and Paululat, 2016).

Ostial cell of the larval dorsal vessel. There are 12 of these cells per dorsal vessel, forming a total of 3 pairs of ostia, which are located in the posterior dorsal vessel (heart) (Lehmacher et al., 2012). It develops from an embryonic ostial cardioblast (Lehmacher et al., 2012). During metamorphosis, the 8 cells forming the two posterior pairs are hystolized and the 4 cells of the anterior-most pair persist to form the posteriormost adult ostia (Lehmacher et al., 2012).

A specialized cardiomyocyte that forms a valve inside the dorsal vessel. There are two of these cells per valve. They have large intracellular vesicles that occupy most of their volume, a high number of mitochondria, and a network-like arrangement of myofilaments (Lehmacher et al., 2012; Rotstein and Paululat, 2016).

Intracardial valve cell of the adult dorsal vessel. There are 6 of these cells per dorsal vessel, forming 3 valves separating the 4 chambers of the adult heart (Lehmacher et al., 2012; Rotstein and Paululat, 2016).
